## What’s New

### Auto-Linking on KB Ingest

Knowledge Base entries are now automatically linked to related existing entries when ingested.

**Four linking strategies:**

| Strategy | Relation Type | Trigger |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Semantic Similarity | SIMILAR\_TO | Cosine similarity >= 0.75 |
| Shared Entities | SHARES\_ENTITY | Jaccard coefficient >= 0.3 |
| Shared Tags | SHARES\_TAG | >= 2 tags in common |
| FTS Topic Overlap | TOPIC\_OVERLAP | Fallback when < 2 edges |

**Key features:** - Automatic edge creation during mem\_ingest and mem\_ingest\_file - Configurable thresholds and max edges per strategy - Direction-agnostic deduplication - Backfill support via mem\_graph action=auto\_link - Ingest response includes auto-link count - Master switch: autoLink.enabled

### Backfill Command

New mem\_graph action auto\_link: - Without entry\_id: processes all orphan entries (0 edges), max 50 per call - With entry\_id: auto-links a specific entry

## Breaking Changes

None. Purely additive feature.

